80  template <typename T>
106  ros::Publisher *AddFeature(std::string featurename = "", unsigned long queuesize = 1)
107  {
108  // Get the next UUID (already saved one or new one if not existing yet) and set the topic name
109  std::string featureUUID = getNextFeatureUUID();
110  ros::Publisher *publisher = 0;
111  std::string publisherName = "/Tapi/" + uuid + "/" + featureUUID;
112 
113  // Create a publisher of the Template-type with the topic name generated above
114  publisher = new ros::Publisher(nh->advertise<T>(publisherName, queuesize));
115 
116  // Publisher created successfully
117  if (publisher)
118  {
119  publishers.push_back(publisher);
120  tapi_lib::Feature feature;
121 
122  // Generate ros::SubscribeOptions with the same type as the publisher to save its message type (only available on
123  // Subscribers/SubscribeOptions but not on Publishers/PublishOptions -> do this workaround)
124  ros::SubscribeOptions temp;
125  temp = ros::SubscribeOptions::create<T>("", 1, NULL, ros::VoidPtr(), NULL);
126  feature.FeatureType = temp.datatype;
127 
128  // Save name and uuid and save the create message in the \c featureMsgs \c vector of Tapi::TapiClient
129  feature.Name = featurename;
130  feature.UUID = featureUUID;
131  featureMsgs.push_back(feature);
132  }
133  connect();
134  return publisher;
135  }
136 
137 private:
138  // Private member variables

144  std::string nodename;
145 
150  std::vector<ros::Publisher *> publishers;
151 };
